  "story_segments": [
    "Astronauts are people ",
    " travel into space to learn more about the stars and planets. Living in a space station is very different from living ",
    " Earth.\n\nThere is no gravity, ",
    " everything floats. This means that astronauts ",
    " to tie their beds to the wall so they don't float away while they are sleeping! They also have to be careful when they are ",
    " because crumbs could get into the machines.\n\nAstronauts ",
    " a lot of time doing experiments. They want to find ",
    " if plants can grow in space or if humans could live on the Moon one day. It is ",
    " difficult job in the world, but it is also very exciting.\n\nIf you want to ",
    " an astronaut, you need to study science and maths very ",
    ". You also have to be very healthy and strong. It's a dream for many children, ",
    " it?"
